{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1999 |Team=South Carolina Gamecocks |Image=South Carolina Gamecocks wordmark.svg |ImageSize=150 |Conference=Southeastern Conference |Division=Eastern Division |ShortConference=SEC |CoachRank= |APRank= |BCSRank= |Record=0-11 |ConfRecord=0-8 |HeadCoach=[[Lou Holtz]] |OffCoach= |DefCoach= |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena=[[Williams-Brice Stadium]] (c. 80,250, grass) |Champion= |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= }} {{1999 SEC football standings}} The '''1999 South Carolina Gamecocks football team''' represented the [[University of South Carolina]] in the [[Southeastern Conference]] during the [[college football]] [[1999 NCAA Division I-A football season|season of 1999-2000]]. The Gamecocks were led by [[Lou Holtz]] in his first season as USC head coach and played their home games in [[Williams-Brice Stadium]] in [[Columbia, South Carolina]].
